<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr>  <br>
My thoughts after a week+ <br>
Warning, severe negativity inside. <br>
<br>
I have tried hard to come here; and speak of the things that are coming. I have tried my best to bite my tongue to all those who would argue with me or flame me for finding use in our new spells. I have largely ignored being a doomsayer and have taken Rich's side alot, and I realize its more comforting to hear it direct as I do than third hand; but I do my best to make sure you guys hear as much as I can give. <br>
<br>
Things have started to settle down this week. Druid CH has become a way of life now, not a novelty test spell. I'm going to clarify that I am going to call this the &quot;Druid CH&quot; and not the &quot;Druid/Shaman CH&quot; because well, largely, this change means nothing to Shamans, for reasons already covered in numerous threads. <br>
<br>
I believe the Druid spell is both wildly unbalancing to their class; and a hugely damaging blow to our class. I have taken my chances to voice that opinion to Rich W; however I don't believe its entirely his decision, and he is a nice guy who is trying to help us, and I don't want to start a &quot;Burn Rich at the Stake&quot; crusade. <br>
<br>
I could go over a list of everything druids have on us; or everything shamans have on us for that matter -- But I'd get no where. We know the differences. The druid community has always been famous for being the community that can Whine in unison and there with recieve everything -- Squeakiest Wheel if you will. <br>
<br>
Instead, all I am going to say is a very concise point of venting, almost laundry list style. After a week+; now that its all settled in, I feel the Druid CH is more of a Cleric change than any of our new spells, and I'm going to comment on that too. <br>
<br>
My tells for groups has dropped to almost zero. My ability to get a group at all depends entirely on me either making the group; or the mercy of my closest friends. The soloing is only useful to me as a tradeskill farming thing; and believe me its gotten alot of use since every druid bot or solo druid got dusted off and given the primary healer spot in the group. CT is not the haven that some think it will be -- Groups are already there every day who are not using a cleric at all. I don't care what you throw out about the numbers, and the caps, and percentages, and efficiency; its all statistics. Statistics don't mean jack sh*t compared to what really happens in the world, and that is that all statistics aside, the heal is working well enough that either class can now be primary healer and still offer their full array of abilities. <br>
<br>
On the flipside; the intention of the spell, raid usage, has not occured. Druids and Shamans are not being put in CH chains. They're not being used to cut down the amount of clerics needed/wanted for a raid; that was largely determined by the size of the chain needed already. We &quot;know our role&quot; on a raid; in that chain we hate so much. That chain is a tried and true method that has been perfected over time and works. No one wants to fool with trying to rework timing and using casting offsets to work a druid into the chain and pray that the cap on the heal doesn't hit at the same time a boss spikes in damage and you lose the MT. You just don't want to waste everyone's time with that kind of a risk, so its still all cleric, all the time. I'm not talking about Avatar of War here either; In fact I've never even seen the AoW. <br>
<br>
I don't pretend to have an answer, either, short of the one I already know will never happen. All I wanted to do was vent minorly this morning. I have said in the past that I believed we were still useful in some groups, and that there were groups where nothing but a GenuineCleric would do. In alot of ways, thats still true, but the areas are already more rare than CT; and they are dwindling further still as comfort level in all players increases with the Druid CH.<br>
<br>
